HEADWORD: Chantey
<hw>Chant"ey</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>chanter</ets> to sing, and <er>Chant</er>. <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>A sailor's song.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>May we lift a deep-sea <qex>chantey</qex> such as seamen use at
sea?</q> <rj><qau>Kipling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

